                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16740360" author="coheigea" created="Fri, 11 Jan 2019 12:59:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll remove this code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16740514" author="dkulp" created="Fri, 11 Jan 2019 15:58:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just a note:  with the removal of this, if there are temp files that are locked due to streams not being closed properly, they may remain after shutdown.   The purpose of that line was to hopefully get the file streams and such garbage collected and finalized so that the files can be removed.   With this change, if the delete fails, it will likely just keep the files around.  (and this is really just Windows issue as all the unix&apos;s can delete open files)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
